BASF to Invest EU10 Billion in Ludwigshafen, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   S h e e n a g h   M a t t h e w s
-- 
2011-09-16T06:18:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/basf-to-invest-eu10-billion-in-ludwigshafen-handelsblatt-says.html
BASF SE (BAS)  plans to invest as much as
10 billion euros ($13.9 billion) by 2015 in the sustainability
of its main production site in Ludwigshafen,  Germany ,
 Handelsblatt said , citing an interview with executive board
member Margret Suckale.  About two-thirds of the investment will be used to expand
current factories, Suckale said, according to the German
newspaper. BASF is already building new factories in
Ludwigshafen for insulating materials, softening agents and
aroma chemicals, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sheenagh Matthews in Frankfurt at 
 smatthews6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net  